  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Towards Inclusive and Sustainable Industries: Capacity Building Programme for Professionals from Africa and the Arab region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme, which will be conducted in cooperation with the University of Bahrain and the UNIDO Investment and Technology Promotion Office (ITPO) / Arab International Center for Entrepreneurship  &amp; Investment (AICEI) in Bahrain, targets young professionals from Arab and African states in the fields of resource efficient and cleaner production (RECP), industrial energy efficiency and renewable energy, members of non-governmental organizations involved in environmental advocacy, and young and middle
level academics and PhD students with a background in technical or policy studies in related fields.
It aims to give participants the opportunity to reflect on how to improve their countries&#x2019; industrial performance, thus generating more decent employment opportunities for the local labor force, while increasing its environmental sustainability. Participants will ponder on various strategies and transition plans for countries, specific sectors and companies towards Green Industry and how to fit them with the over-all goal of ISID.</narrative>
  </description>
